Predictive decisioning
300-level live demo

  • Demo preparation
  • Demo script
DEMO OVERVIEW
Scenario overviewThis demo shows the integration of prediction services inside rules-based decisions and how Cloud Pak for Business Automation leverages intelligent decisions to deliver rapidly new applications. This scenario is not willing to explain in detail what rules are, and it is not in the scope of the scenario to go deep inside Automation Decision Services’s rule management capabilities. The focus of the demo is really around the artificial intelligence (AI)/machine learning (ML) native integration. It is also in the scope of this demo to show the power of Cloud Pak for Business Automation to create low-code interfaces from where Automation Decision Services will be consumed and valorized.

This demo is 100% based on IBM technology:
1. Watson Machine Learning
2. Cloud Pak for Business Automation
Demo productsCloud Pak for Business Automation V21.0.1, Cloud Pak for Data and AI
Demo capabilitiesBusiness Rule Automation, Predictive Services Integration, Rapid Application Development
Demo guidanceThis demo script has multiple tasks, that each have multiple steps. In each step, you have the details about what you need to do (Actions), what you can say while delivering this demo step (Narration), and what diagrams and screenshots you will see (Screenshots). This demo script is a suggestion, and you are welcome to customize based on your sales opportunity. Most importantly, practice this demo in advance. If the demo seems easy for you to execute, the customer will focus on the content. If it seems difficult for you to execute, the customer will focus on your delivery.
How to get supportContact #itz-techzone-support regarding issues with reserving and provisioning TechZone environments.

Contact #platinumdemos-automation-support regarding issues with setting up and running this demo use case.

These files will be referenced in the steps below.



PREPARE TO GIVE THE DEMO

The setup process is illustrated in the following chart. Each number icon corresponds to the respective preparation step below.

1 - Provision your demo environment

You must install Cloud Pak for Business Automation 21.0.1 or provision a ROKS environment that will be available for 2 weeks at no charge.
The steps below explain how to get a free pre-configured Cloud Pak for Business Automation environment:

Reserve your CP4BA preconfigured environment on ROKS
  1. Log in to the IBM Technology Zone using your IBM ID. Then, click on the Activation Kits tab.



  1. Scroll down to click on the Cloud Pak for Business Automation tile.



  1. Click on the Environments - Reserve Here! tab. Then, select the Reserve Here! - Cloud Pak for Business Automation OpenShift Demo Environments tile.

  2. Click on the Preinstalled OpenShift Environments tab. Then, select the latest version of the Preinstalled Cloud Pak for Business Automation on Red Hat OpenShift on IBM Cloud.

  3. Select Reserve now. Then, after entering the Purpose, Preferred Geography, and Notes, click on Submit.

  4. When you are done, you will see a confirmation message. In addition, you will receive a confirmation email with all the access links.





  1. Then, you will receive an email confirming that your instance is provisioned. It may take 30 to 45 minutes.

  2. At the top right corner, click on the Profile icon. Then, click on Reservations. You will then be directed to the My reservations page, in which you can see your reservation details. Note: Bookmark this page for ease of reference.

The API key provides your personal credentials and allows an external application to connect to your deployment workspace in IBM Watson Studio.

If you already have an API key, you can reuse it. Otherwise, you will need a new one. To get a new API key, please follow the steps below.

  1. Connect to your IBM Cloud instance.

  2. Click on the Manage menu, and select Access (IAM).



  1. Select API keys.



  1. Click on Create an IBM Cloud API Key.



  1. Enter a name and description for the API key. Then, click on Create.



  1. You can unmask the API key to view it. This API key is required for your machine learning provider setup. You can directly copy it to your clipboard or download the API key locally and keep it for other uses.

Troubleshooting

Q: I don’t see the deployed decision service.

A: If you don’t see the Telco retention decision service, it may be due to an incomplete deployment phase. Make sure that you have published your deployed decision service in Automation Decision Services. Refer to the deployment steps in 6 - Deploy and publish your decision service.

Q: I get an error when I launch the service after a reconnection.

A: After reconfiguring your service connection, you may have some errors when you invoke your service during the preview. It may be due to some cash authorization access problems. It should work after you clean all of your browser’s cache data (including cookies) and restart Application Designer.

Q: My decision service is deployed but with a different name.

A: You will have to bind the decision node in Application Designer to your deployed service by following the steps below:

  1. Click on Open in your application tile.

  2. Click on your user icon image, and open Preferences.



  1. Select the Advanced view mode. Note: You may have to restart after this.



  1. Click on the Diagram tab, in which you should see the application diagram.



  1. Double-click on the Call telco_retention_ds box.

  2. Select the Implementation tab. Click on Select, and select your own decision service. Make sure you also select the retentionOffer operation.



  1. Go in the Data Mapping section, and make sure the local variables are linked to your service input/output.



  1. If you have errors, it may be due to the import that caused duplications (ex: CustomerRecord_1). You must then make sure that the variables are from that new class to allow the data mapping.

  2. Click on the Variables tab, and select the customer (CustomerRecord). Select the duplicated type in the Variable type section. It should now be customer (CustomerRecord_1) type.



  1. Repeat these steps for the subscription class.

  2. Return to the Diagram view.

  3. Reconnect your input and output data to map the new service type. You should now have no errors. Click on Preview and test the connection.

Reconnect the Telco Retention Application to the new decision service
  1. Open Application Designer, and open the Telco Retention Application.



  1. Click on the Diagram tab, and select the Call telco_retention… node.





  1. Select the Implementation tab. Note the name of the actual decision service. Here in this example, it is telco_retention_ds_Service.


  1. Click New to select the newly published decision service.

  2. Select the new decision service from the published services list.



  1. Select the retentionOffer operation.



  1. In the operation combo, select the retentionOffer operation.



  1. The data mapping must be redone. Since the new service has the same complex name types, Application Designer has automatically renamed the customer and subscription types by adding ”_1” to the names of the types.



  1. Click on the icon on the left of the yellow arrow, and select the customer variable.





  1. An error will appear due to the renaming.



  1. Select the subscription variable under Input Mapping as well. Another error will appear.





  1. Under Output Mapping, select the message and estimated_cost variables.



  1. Let’s now solve the variable name change issue. Go in the Variables tab, and select the customer variable.



  1. Click on Select in the Variable type field, and select the option with the ”_1” (customerRecord_1 in our case).



  1. Repeat steps 13 and 14 for the subscription variable.



  1. Return to the Diagram tab, and click on the Call telco_retention… node again. Take a look at the Data Mapping tab to see that the errors are gone.



  1. We can optionally remove the original decision service that we noted in step 3.



  1. Click on Preview to test the connection. Selecting Sarah Miller must return the result below.



  1. You are ready to demo. Note: Remember to undeploy your machine learning models in IBM Watson Studio after the demo to avoid being overcharged.
